<doc id="1084174" wikidata="Q5167581" url="?curid=1084174" title="Coombe, Gwennap">
<text>Coombe () is a settlement in Gwennap civil parish, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom. It is situated approximately three-and-a-half miles (6 km) southeast of Redruth at .

The name &#x27;Komm&#x27; in Cornish means &#x27;small valley, dingle&#x27;. Compare the Welsh &#x27;cwm&#x27;.

