<doc id="1084282" wikidata="Q703853" url="?curid=1084282" title="Weddersleben">
<text>Weddersleben is a village and a former municipality in the district of Harz, Saxony-Anhalt, in the Harz area. Since 1 January 2009, it is part of the town Thale.

The village is well known for being located adjacent to the famed natural rock formation known as the Teufelsmauer, or &quot;Devil&#x27;s Wall&quot; in English. Surrounding forest area has numerous paths for biking and hiking, making it a popular tourist destination for nature seekers. Among the many natural formations in the area, the Bode River flows by the edges of the village.</text><links>
<link wikidata="Q6087" start="59" end="75" title="Harz (district)" label="district of Harz"/>
